 <span dir="ltr">Mel</span>  said...</dt>
<dd><p>I'm sure what people are responding to is how well the photographer has distilled what was there into such a strong and simple looking composition. Unfortunately, this leads them to believe that there's nothing to it, and the camera gets all the credit! There's no denying that we do use nice cameras, but it'd be better for our sanity if the compliment were paid another way. (Like buying a print!)If it really were that easy, there's no way I'd be as addicted to photography as I am...</p>
<p class="comment-timestamp">12 June 2007 13:27</p>

<div class="r"></div></dd> <dt id="c1390556161495157796">
<img src="/img/b16-rounded.gif" class="comment-icon" alt="Blogger">
 <span dir="ltr"><a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/12597110929479917422" onclick="window.open(this.href);return false;" rel="nofollow">Tim</a></span>  said...</dt>
<dd><p>What he doesn't understand is that making it look so easy is in fact so bloody difficult.</p>
<p class="comment-timestamp">28 June 2007 21:45</p>

<div class="r"></div></dd>
